Beese Fulmer Investment Management Inc. Has $719,000 Position in Eaton Corporation, PLC (NYSE:ETN)

Posted by David Goldstein on Jul 23rd, 2017 // No Comments 

Beese Fulmer Investment Management Inc. maintained its stake in shares of Eaton Corporation, PLC (NYSE:ETN) during the second quarter, according to its most recent filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission. The fund owned 9,237 shares of the industrial products company’s stock at the end of the second quarter. Beese Fulmer Investment Management Inc.’s holdings in Eaton Corporation, PLC were worth $719,000 as of its most recent SEC filing. 
Several other hedge funds have also recently modified their holdings of the company. Massmutual Trust Co. FSB ADV raised its stake in Eaton Corporation, PLC by 9.4% in the first quarter. Massmutual Trust Co. FSB ADV now owns 1,402 shares of the industrial products company’s stock valued at $104,000 after buying an additional 120 shares in the last quarter. Harfst & Associates Inc. bought a new stake in Eaton Corporation, PLC during the first quarter valued at about $109,000. Tompkins Financial Corp bought a new stake in Eaton Corporation, PLC during the first quarter valued at about $124,000. Guardian Life Insurance Co. of America raised its stake in Eaton Corporation, PLC by 0.7% in the first quarter. Guardian Life Insurance Co. of America now owns 1,742 shares of the industrial products company’s stock valued at $129,000 after buying an additional 12 shares in the last quarter. Finally, Crestwood Advisors Group LLC bought a new stake in Eaton Corporation, PLC during the first quarter valued at about $137,000. 76.30% of the stock is owned by institutional investors. 


 Get Eaton Corporation PLC alerts:



Eaton Corporation, PLC (NYSE:ETN) opened at 78.97 on Friday. The stock has a market capitalization of $35.32 billion, a P/E ratio of 18.40 and a beta of 1.35. Eaton Corporation, PLC has a 12 month low of $59.07 and a 12 month high of $81.63. The stock has a 50 day moving average price of $77.76 and a 200 day moving average price of $74.22. 




Eaton Corporation, PLC (NYSE:ETN) last posted its earnings results on Tuesday, May 2nd. The industrial products company reported $0.96 EPS for the quarter, beating the Zacks’ consensus estimate of $0.87 by $0.09. Eaton Corporation, PLC had a return on equity of 12.82% and a net margin of 9.86%. The firm had revenue of $4.85 billion for the quarter, compared to analysts’ expectations of $4.70 billion. During the same period last year, the firm earned $0.88 EPS. The company’s quarterly revenue was up .7% on a year-over-year basis. Equities analysts predict that Eaton Corporation, PLC will post $4.66 EPS for the current fiscal year. 
